Out: 0123

Do this:

Convert the string to integer, taking care to include the two hex digits,
Then use XOR to remove the two hex digits.  (You may wish to use an XOR mask, XOR_AND, to keep them from being removed).
Convert the integer to a binary string again, this time including the two hex digits, since your input does not represent any valid binary string (or at most one byte, which is what XOR is for).
Add the two hex digits to the string, and then the XOR of the two hex digits to their respective characters, leaving the binary string unchanged.

